In November 2015 we launched translate-apex.com website. This project is the collection of free translations of APEX Internal Messages to help APEX Community developing applications in other than 10 default languages. The website allows you to browse translations (over 40 different languages available so far), download installation script for any APEX version starting from 3.0 and share your translation with others. All translations are available for free and have been created by APEX Community.

During the presentation I will:
- tell about the project, its history, creation process and plan for the future;
- tell how we have found and connected over 40 APEX Developers from all over the world to collaborate in this project, stressing strength and internationalism of APEX Community;
- speak about technical issues that we faced (including translation process, RTL support, verification of received translations etc.);
- show how you can use it in your own APEX application;
- show open source APEX applications that are integrated with translate-apex.com and allow you to install and manage translations in your APEX environment.

